Expected-output regeneration for the quadbin pg_regress suite.

The run_compare harness (mobilitydb/test/scripts/test.cmake) diffs the
byte-exact psql `-e` transcript of each queries/<name>.test.sql against
expected/<name>.test.out. The harness configures the test cluster with a fixed
locale so transcripts are reproducible across machines:

  timezone = 'America/Los_Angeles'
  datestyle = 'Postgres, MDY'

so timestamps render as e.g. `@Sun Jan 01 08:00:00 2012 PST`. Regenerate the
goldens through the harness (not a hand-run psql, whose timezone/datestyle
differ) and review every diff line before committing:

  ctest -R quadbin            # produces build/tmptest/out/<name>.out
  cp build/tmptest/out/<name>.out mobilitydb/test/quadbin/expected/<name>.test.out

305_quadbin_golden.test.out is the kernel golden-vector file: every statement
is a single boolean assertion that evaluates to `t` against the CARTO
quadbin-py reference values (quadbin_tile_to_cell / quadbin_cell_to_tile /
quadbin_point_to_cell / quadbin_cell_to_parent). A failed assertion there is a
kernel regression. The remaining files transcribe quadbin/quadbinset and
tquadbin I/O, the operators, and the lifted cell operations, including the
deliberate negative cases (invalid-cell parse, type-safety, typmod errors).
